00:00:01,470 --> 00:00:03,790
Lesson 57

2
00:00:03,790 --> 00:00:06,610
An unusual day

3
00:00:06,610 --> 00:00:12,490
Listen to the tape then answer this question.

4
00:00:12,490 --> 00:00:18,080
What is Mr. Sawyer doing tonight?

5
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:20,730
It is eight o'clock.

6
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:24,820
The children go to school by car every day,

7
00:00:24,820 --> 00:00:30,950
but today, they are going to school on foot.

8
00:00:30,950 --> 00:00:33,740
It is ten o'clock.

9
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:38,310
Mrs. Sawyer usually stays at home in the morning,

10
00:00:38,310 --> 00:00:44,230
but this morning, she is going to the shops.

11
00:00:44,230 --> 00:00:47,520
It is four o'clock.

12
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:54,320
In the afternoon, Mrs. Sawyer usually drinks tea in the living room.

13
00:00:54,320 --> 00:01:00,730
But this afternoon, she is drinking tea in the garden.

14
00:01:00,730 --> 00:01:03,100
It is six o'clock.

15
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:07,880
In the evening, the children usually do their homework,

16
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:11,990
but this evening, they are not doing their homework.

17
00:01:11,990 --> 00:01:17,150
At the moment, they are playing in the garden.

18
00:01:17,150 --> 00:01:19,660
It is nine o'clock.

19
00:01:19,660 --> 00:01:24,490
Mr. Sawyer usually reads his newspaper at night.

20
00:01:24,490 --> 00:01:28,610
But he's not reading his newspaper tonight.

21
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:29,610
At the moment, he's reading an interesting book.
